│                                                                               │
│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The crash occurs after the loop-fusion pass rewires control flow, and the     │
│ LLVM verifier reports a malformed PHI node in the second loop's preheader     │
│ (for.end). Specifically, the PHI in the preheader still has incoming from the │
│ first loop's exiting block (%for.inc), but after fusion, the preheader's      │
│ predecessor set changes (now includes %for.inc6 as well), which causes the    │
│ "PHI node entries do not match predecessors" verifier error and ultimately    │
│ the SIGABRT.                                                                  │
│                                                                               │
│ The debug log shows loop-fusion sinking preheader instructions and then       │
│ performing fusion, but it attempts to sink PHI nodes like %sum1.0.lcssa from  │
│ the second loop's preheader into the second loop's exit block. This is        │
│ incorrect because PHI nodes cannot be moved to a different block except at    │
│ the start of their own block. Moving PHIs as regular instructions corrupts    │
│ the IR, and even if they were not moved, subsequent CFG rewiring leaves the   │
│ PHI's incoming edges inconsistent with the new predecessors.                  │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ - The pass identifies that the second candidate's preheader is non-empty and  │
│ tries to hoist and sink its instructions.                                     │
│ - The log explicitly shows the PHI in the preheader considered for sinking:   │
│ "Checking Inst:   %sum1.0.lcssa = phi i32 [ %add, %for.inc ]\n\tCould not     │
│ hoist. Trying to sink...\n\tSafe to sink.".                                   │
│ - The fusion is performed after hoist/sink, but the verifier then trips on    │
│ the PHI in for.end: the preheader now has predecessors for.inc and for.inc6,  │
│ while the PHI still only has the incoming for.inc, hence mismatch.            │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ - The function movePreheaderInsts attempts to sink preheader instructions,    │
│ including PHI nodes, by moving them with I->moveBefore(...) into              │
│ FC1.ExitBlock. This is invalid for PHI nodes.                                 │
│ - Even if sinking were deferred, the subsequent CFG changes (performFusion)   │
│ invalidate the PHI's predecessor list unless it is removed or rewritten.      │
│ - Therefore, PHI nodes in FC1.Preheader must be handled specially: they are   │
│ LCSSA PHIs carrying values from the preceding loop into the rest of the       │
│ function. Since FC1.Preheader has a single incoming edge originally, these    │
│ PHIs can be eliminated by replacing their uses with the unique incoming value │
│ before any CFG rewiring. This preserves semantics and avoids illegal PHI      │
│ motion.                                                                       │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s)                                                     │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/LoopFuse.cpp                               │
│ - Location: In movePreheaderInsts (around lines 1450-1484), before moving     │
│ hoist/sink instructions, add special handling to eliminate PHI nodes from     │
│ FC1.Preheader by replacing their uses with their unique incoming value and    │
│ erasing them.                                                                 │
│                                                                               │
│ Edit (replace the body of movePreheaderInsts to insert PHI handling before    │
│ the loops that move HoistInsts/SinkInsts):                                    │
│                                                                               │
│   void movePreheaderInsts(const FusionCandidate &FC0,                         │
│                           const FusionCandidate &FC1,                         │
│                           SmallVector<Instruction *, 4> &HoistInsts,          │
│                           SmallVector<Instruction *, 4> &SinkInsts) const {   │
│     // All preheader instructions except the branch must be hoisted or sunk   │
│     assert(HoistInsts.size() + SinkInsts.size() == FC1.Preheader->size() - 1  │
│ &&                                                                            │
│            "Attempting to sink and hoist preheader instructions, but not all  │
│ "                                                                             │
│            "the preheader instructions are accounted for.");                  │
│                                                                               │
│     // PHI nodes cannot be moved across blocks. The preheader PHIs here are   │
│     // LCSSA PHIs with a single incoming edge. Before rewiring the CFG,       │
│     // replace their uses with their unique incoming value and erase them.    │
│     while (PHINode *PN = dyn_cast<PHINode>(&FC1.Preheader->front())) {        │
│       // Expect a single incoming since preheader is a single-predecessor     │
│ block                                                                         │
│       // in simplified/rotated form. Use the only incoming value.             │
│       assert(PN->getNumIncomingValues() == 1 &&                               │
│              "Expected single-incoming LCSSA PHI in preheader");              │
│       Value *InVal = PN->getIncomingValue(0);                                 │
│       PN->replaceAllUsesWith(InVal);                                          │
│       PN->eraseFromParent();                                                  │
│     }                                                                         │
│                                                                               │
│     NumHoistedInsts += HoistInsts.size();                                     │
│     NumSunkInsts += SinkInsts.size();                                         │
│                                                                               │
│     LLVM_DEBUG(if (VerboseFusionDebugging) {                                  │
│       if (!HoistInsts.empty())                                                │
│         dbgs() << "Hoisting: \n";                                             │
│       for (Instruction *I : HoistInsts)                                       │
│         dbgs() << *I << "\n";                                                 │
│       if (!SinkInsts.empty())                                                 │
│         dbgs() << "Sinking: \n";                                              │
│       for (Instruction *I : SinkInsts)                                        │
│         dbgs() << *I << "\n";                                                 │
│     });                                                                       │
│                                                                               │
│     for (Instruction *I : HoistInsts) {                                       │
│       assert(I->getParent() == FC1.Preheader);                                │
│       I->moveBefore(*FC0.Preheader,                                           │
│                     FC0.Preheader->getTerminator()->getIterator());           │
│     }                                                                         │
│     // insert instructions in reverse order to maintain dominance             │
│ relationship                                                                  │
│     for (Instruction *I : reverse(SinkInsts)) {                               │
│       assert(I->getParent() == FC1.Preheader);                                │
│       // PHIs were already removed above; remaining instructions are non-PHI. │
│       I->moveBefore(*FC1.ExitBlock, FC1.ExitBlock->getFirstInsertionPt());    │
│     }                                                                         │
│   }                                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ Rationale:                                                                    │
│ - This change ensures PHI nodes are not moved illegally. By replacing their   │
│ uses with the unique incoming value and erasing them early, we avoid later    │
│ verifier failures caused by mismatched predecessor lists when the CFG is      │
│ updated during fusion.                                                        │
│ - It is consistent with the semantics of LCSSA PHIs in a preheader with a     │
│ single predecessor and with the pass's assumption that loops are in           │
│ simplified and rotated form.                                                  │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ The crash is caused by attempting to sink PHI nodes from the preheader as     │
│ generic instructions, which is invalid and leads to inconsistent PHI          │
│ predecessors after CFG rewiring. By explicitly removing preheader PHI nodes   │
│ before hoist/sink and fusion—replacing their uses with the single incoming    │
│ value—we preserve correctness and prevent the verifier assertion. This fix    │
│ targets the first transformation point that modified IR (movePreheaderInsts   │
│ followed by performFusion) and aligns with the pass's preconditions.          │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                               │
