│ Proposed fix summary:                                                         │
│ - Avoid illegally moving PHI nodes in movePreheaderInsts. PHIs must remain at │
│ the start of their block; we now skip moving any PHI included in the          │
│ hoist/sink lists, leaving them in the preheader. This prevents creating       │
│ malformed IR when CFG is rewired during fusion.                               │
│                                                                               │
│ Patch details:                                                                │
│ - Updated movePreheaderInsts in llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/LoopFuse.cpp to:   │
│   - Keep existing assertion unchanged.                                        │
│   - Skip PHI nodes when performing the actual moves for both hoist and sink   │
│ paths, ensuring PHIs are not moved across blocks.                             │
│                                                                               │
│ This change addresses the verifier crash by preventing PHIs from being moved  │
│ to another block, which previously caused predecessor mismatches post-fusion. │
